### ========================================
### CONFIGURACIÓN
### ========================================
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5270
@contentType = application/json

### ========================================
### 📝 PASO 1: CREAR USUARIOS
### ========================================

### 1.1 Crear usuario PMO (copia el ID de la respuesta)
# @name userPMO
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "entraObjectId": "pmo-user-001",
  "email": "maria.pmo@university.edu",
  "firstName": "María",
  "lastName": "González",
  "role": "PMO",
  "isActive": true
}

### 1.2 Crear usuario Team (copia el ID de la respuesta)
# @name userTeam
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "entraObjectId": "team-user-001",
  "email": "juan.team@university.edu",
  "firstName": "Juan",
  "lastName": "Pérez",
  "role": "Team",
  "isActive": true
}

### 1.3 Verificar usuarios creados
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users

### 1.4 🧪 TEST: Intentar crear usuario con rol inválido (debe fallar)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "entraObjectId": "invalid-user",
  "email": "invalid@university.edu",
  "firstName": "Invalid",
  "lastName": "User",
  "role": "SuperAdmin",
  "isActive": true
}

### ========================================
### 🏢 PASO 2: CREAR ENTIDADES
### ========================================

### 2.1 Crear entidad raíz (copia el ID de la respuesta)
# @name entityRoot
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/entities
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Dirección de Investigación",
  "code": "DIR-INV",
  "description": "Dirección de Investigación y Posgrado",
  "isActive": true
}

### 2.2 Crear entidad hija (usa el ID del paso 2.1)
# @name entityChild
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/entities
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Departamento de Sistemas",
  "code": "DEPT-SIS",
  "description": "Departamento de Ingeniería en Sistemas",
  "parentEntityId": "69d5a8aec913608aff1ddb57",
  "isActive": true
}

### 2.3 Verificar entidades
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/entities

### 2.4 Buscar por código
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/entities/code/DIR-INV

### 2.5 Obtener hijos de la entidad raíz (usa ID de 2.1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/entities/children/69d5a8aec913608aff1ddb57

### 2.6 🧪 TEST: Código duplicado (debe fallar con 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/entities
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Otra dirección",
  "code": "DIR-INV",
  "description": "Código duplicado",
  "isActive": true
}

### ========================================
### 📋 PASO 3: CREAR TRACKING REQUEST
### ========================================

### 3.1 Crear solicitud de seguimiento (copia el ID de la respuesta)
# Usa el ID de la entidad del paso 2.1
# @name trackingRequest
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/trackingrequests
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Reporte de Publicaciones Q2 2026",
  "description": "Seguimiento mensual de publicaciones científicas",
  "goalType": "Publicaciones Científicas",
  "targetEntityIds": ["69d5a8aec913608aff1ddb57"],
  "startDate": "2026-04-15",
  "dueDate": "2026-06-30",
  "frequency": "Mensual",
  "isRecurring": true
}

### 3.2 Obtener todas las solicitudes en proceso
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/trackingrequests/in-progress

### 3.3 Obtener mis solicitudes (como PMO)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/trackingrequests/my-requests

### 3.4 🧪 TEST: Fechas inválidas (debe fallar)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/trackingrequests
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Solicitud inválida",
  "description": "DueDate antes de StartDate",
  "goalType": "Test",
  "targetEntityIds": ["507f1f77bcf86cd799439011"],
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "dueDate": "2026-05-01",
  "frequency": null,
  "isRecurring": false
}

### 3.5 Actualizar tracking request a status Active
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/trackingrequests/69d5a9a8c913608aff1ddb59
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Reporte de Publicaciones Q2 2026",
  "description": "Seguimiento mensual de publicaciones científicas",
  "goalType": "Publicaciones Científicas",
  "targetEntityIds": ["69d5a8aec913608aff1ddb57"],
  "startDate": "2026-04-15",
  "dueDate": "2026-06-30",
  "frequency": "Mensual",
  "isRecurring": true,
  "status": "InProgress"
}

### 3.6 Verificar que ahora tiene status InProgress
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/trackingrequests/in-progress

### 3.7 🧪 TEST: Status inválido (debe fallar)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/trackingrequests/69d5a9a8c913608aff1ddb59
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Reporte de Publicaciones Q2 2026",
  "description": "Seguimiento mensual de publicaciones científicas",
  "goalType": "Publicaciones Científicas",
  "targetEntityIds": ["69d5a8aec913608aff1ddb57"],
  "startDate": "2026-04-15",
  "dueDate": "2026-06-30",
  "frequency": "Mensual",
  "isRecurring": true,
  "status": "InvalidStatus"
}

### ========================================
### 📌 PASO 4: CREAR ASSIGNMENT
### ========================================

### 4.1 Crear asignación (copia el ID de la respuesta)
# Usa IDs de 3.1 (requestId) y 2.1 (entityId)
# @name assignment
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/requestassignments
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "requestId": "REEMPLAZA-CON-ID-DE-3.1",
  "assignedToEntityId": "REEMPLAZA-CON-ID-DE-2.1",
  "assignedToUserId": "REEMPLAZA-CON-ID-DE-1.2"
}

### 4.2 Ver mis asignaciones
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/requestassignments/my-assignments

### 4.3 Ver asignaciones pendientes
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/requestassignments/pending

### ========================================
### ✍️ PASO 5: CREAR ACTIVIDAD
### ========================================

### 5.1 Crear actividad (copia el ID de la respuesta)
# Usa IDs de 4.1 (assignmentId) y 3.1 (requestId)
# @name activity
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/activities
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "assignmentId": "REEMPLAZA-CON-ID-DE-4.1",
  "requestId": "REEMPLAZA-CON-ID-DE-3.1",
  "description": "Reunión con investigadores para definir plan de publicaciones del trimestre",
  "activityDate": "2026-04-20"
}

### 5.2 Ver mis actividades
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/activities/my-activities

### 5.3 Ver actividades editables
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/activities/editable

### 5.4 Submit actividad (usa ID de 5.1)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/activities/REEMPLAZA-CON-ID-DE-5.1/submit

### 5.5 🧪 TEST: Intentar editar actividad ya submitted (debe fallar)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/activities/REEMPLAZA-CON-ID-DE-5.1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "assignmentId": "REEMPLAZA-CON-ID-DE-4.1",
  "requestId": "REEMPLAZA-CON-ID-DE-3.1",
  "description": "Intentando editar después de submit",
  "activityDate": "2026-04-21"
}

### ========================================
### ✅ PASO 6: CREAR REVIEW
### ========================================

### 6.1 Crear review
# Usa IDs de 4.1 (assignmentId) y 3.1 (requestId)
# @name review
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reviews
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "assignmentId": "REEMPLAZA-CON-ID-DE-4.1",
  "requestId": "REEMPLAZA-CON-ID-DE-3.1",
  "reviewedByUserId": "REEMPLAZA-CON-ID-DE-1.1",
  "decision": "Approved",
  "comments": "Excelente trabajo, cumple con todos los requisitos establecidos"
}

### 6.2 Ver reviews de la asignación (usa ID de 4.1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reviews/assignment/REEMPLAZA-CON-ID-DE-4.1

### ========================================
### 🔔 PASO 7: NOTIFICACIONES
### ========================================

### 7.1 Crear notificación (usa ID de 1.2)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/notifications
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "userId": "REEMPLAZA-CON-ID-DE-1.2",
  "type": "assignment_created",
  "title": "Nueva asignación recibida",
  "message": "Se te ha asignado la solicitud: Reporte de Publicaciones Q2 2026"
}

### 7.2 Ver mis notificaciones
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/notifications

### 7.3 Ver conteo de no leídas
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/notifications/unread/count

### 7.4 Marcar todas como leídas
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/notifications/read-all

### ========================================
### ✅ VALIDACIÓN FINAL
### ========================================

### 8.1 Verificar usuarios
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users

### 8.2 Verificar entidades
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/entities

### 8.3 Verificar solicitudes
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/trackingrequests

### 8.4 Verificar asignaciones
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/requestassignments

### 8.5 Verificar actividades
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/activities

### 8.6 Verificar reviews
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reviews

### 8.7 Verificar notificaciones
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/notifications